lead_paragraph: One New-Orleans mail has arrived--the last still due. The United States sloop of war Cyane received her officers and men on bound yesterday and was put in commission. Commender Franklin Buchanan has been ordered to duty to the Gosport navy-yard. The Norfolk Herald says the new steamer Roanoke, running between New-York and Richmond, went ashore yesterday on a small bar in James River; on her passage from Richmond for New-York.

headline.main: Arrival of the Southern Mail--Commission of U. S. Sloop Cyaue--Steamer Roanoke Ashore.
